<i>(singing)</i>

93
00:04:48,870 --> 00:04:50,760
<i>(singing continues)
No!</i>

94
00:04:50,750 --> 00:04:52,530
<i>(singing continues)
Don't listen to it!</i>

95
00:04:53,750 --> 00:04:55,590
<i>(singing continues)
All aboard?</i>

96
00:04:55,590 --> 00:04:58,840
<i>(singing continues)
Yee Haw! It's roundup time!</i>

97
00:04:58,840 --> 00:05:00,460
<i>(singing continues)
Let's burn rubber.</i>

98
00:05:03,710 --> 00:05:07,460
All power back -
Full speed ahead!

99
00:05:09,940 --> 00:05:11,190
<i>(singing continues)
Batter up!</i>

100
00:05:13,020 --> 00:05:14,940
<i>(singing continues)
It's a wide-end run.</i>

101
00:05:14,940 --> 00:05:18,060
<i>(singing continues)
He's on the 50, the 40, the 30!</i>

102
00:05:19,900 --> 00:05:22,460
(laughs)

103
00:05:28,070 --> 00:05:29,650
I've got to get out
of here.

104
00:05:29,660 --> 00:05:31,000
I've just got to.

105
00:05:35,750 --> 00:05:38,800
Gotta get out.
Gotta get out.

106
00:05:40,670 --> 00:05:42,560
Oh, I am out.

107
00:05:47,170 --> 00:05:47,890
(grunts)

108
00:05:51,840 --> 00:05:52,840
Hey, look!

109
00:05:52,850 --> 00:05:54,520
- Hey!
- Over here.

110
00:05:54,510 --> 00:05:57,510
(All)
There she is! Look!
Yeah, I see her!

111
00:05:57,520 --> 00:05:58,740
What do you want?

112
00:05:58,740 --> 00:06:00,580
Have you seen the ponies?

113
00:06:00,570 --> 00:06:02,570
They're in there,
and they're all playing.

114
00:06:03,190 --> 00:06:04,690
What?

115
00:06:04,690 --> 00:06:07,910
Somnambula made me
sing them into a trance.

116
00:06:07,910 --> 00:06:09,910
Who's Somnambula?

117
00:06:09,910 --> 00:06:11,190
She's an awful witch,

118
00:06:11,200 --> 00:06:14,420
who takes the youth for herself
and only gives back age.

119
00:06:14,420 --> 00:06:16,680
Y-you put them in a trance?

120
00:06:16,670 --> 00:06:18,530
Can you put them out of it?

121
00:06:18,540 --> 00:06:21,380
Well, I suppose I could sing a
different song,

122
00:06:21,370 --> 00:06:23,260
but I'm not going back there.

123
00:06:23,260 --> 00:06:26,380
I'm not going anywhere
near Somnambula again.

124
00:06:26,380 --> 00:06:27,710
But you have to help us.

125
00:06:27,710 --> 00:06:28,960
Please!

126
00:06:28,970 --> 00:06:30,890
Help rescue our friends.

127
00:06:30,880 --> 00:06:32,770
(All)
Yeah, help us! Please!

128
00:06:32,770 --> 00:06:34,930
Okay...I'll help.

129
00:06:34,940 --> 00:06:36,150
Will you come with me?

130
00:06:36,140 --> 00:06:37,440
(All)
YES!

131
00:06:39,940 --> 00:06:43,060
Okay, no one's around.

132
00:06:43,060 --> 00:06:44,940
Cover your ears.

133
00:06:44,950 --> 00:06:49,910
<i>(Kyrie singing)</i>

134
00:06:49,900 --> 00:06:51,870
<i>(singing continues)
The Ponies!</i>

135
00:06:51,870 --> 00:06:53,120
<i>(singing continues)
Got to help them!</i>

136
00:06:54,660 --> 00:06:56,880
<i>(singing continues)
What am I doin'?</i>

137
00:06:58,130 --> 00:07:01,250
You came!
You rescued us.

138
00:07:01,250 --> 00:07:03,310
Our heroes.

139
00:07:03,300 --> 00:07:06,420
But what's happened to us?

140
00:07:06,420 --> 00:07:08,920
We're so old.

141
00:07:08,920 --> 00:07:09,920
Where's Buttons?

142
00:07:09,920 --> 00:07:11,890
I can't find her.

143
00:07:11,890 --> 00:07:15,060
Yeah! I haven't
seen any of the unicorns.

144
00:07:16,350 --> 00:07:18,940
And you won't, either.

145
00:07:24,070 --> 00:07:26,690
4-Speed, Slugger,
come with me.

146
00:07:26,690 --> 00:07:28,940
The rest of you -
protect the Little Ponies.

147
00:07:28,940 --> 00:07:30,570
And bring that bird.

148
00:07:35,580 --> 00:07:36,280
You heard him.

149
00:07:36,280 --> 00:07:37,950
Let's get down to business.

150
00:07:37,950 --> 00:07:39,200
Yee-Haw!

151
00:07:40,450 --> 00:07:41,580
Let's break it down.

152
00:07:43,540 --> 00:07:44,790
Aaaagh!

153
00:07:46,040 --> 00:07:47,290
Let's try again.

154
00:07:47,290 --> 00:07:51,630
Now you'll know what it's like
to have someone gnawin' on you.

155
00:07:56,100 --> 00:07:59,720
Hey, watch where you're goin'!

156
00:08:02,110 --> 00:08:04,150
This is gettin' us nowhere.

157
00:08:04,140 --> 00:08:06,030
We've got to get it open.

158
00:08:06,030 --> 00:08:07,190
Remember Slugger -

159
00:08:07,200 --> 00:08:10,210
Buttons is probably
on the other side.

160
00:08:14,790 --> 00:08:17,250
It's like
all their magic powers

161
00:08:17,240 --> 00:08:19,740
are being sucked
into that crystal.

162
00:08:19,740 --> 00:08:21,320
So...that's it.

163
00:08:21,330 --> 00:08:25,090
Somnambula's been getting
her youth from the other ponies,

164
00:08:25,080 --> 00:08:26,960
and her new powers
from the unicorns.

165
00:08:26,970 --> 00:08:28,840
Quite right, Kyrie!

166
00:08:28,830 --> 00:08:31,630
And I've no intention
of giving them up.

167
00:08:33,390 --> 00:08:35,340
Woo-Wee!

168
00:08:36,590 --> 00:08:40,090
Sing, Kyrie
- wake the unicorns up.

169
00:08:40,100 --> 00:08:42,190
But she can't.

170
00:08:43,400 --> 00:08:46,150
(muffled squeaks)

171
00:08:46,150 --> 00:08:48,020
Then, I'll stop you myself.

172
00:08:49,270 --> 00:08:51,650
Ah...but you won't.

173
00:08:52,910 --> 00:08:54,320
(laughs)

174
00:08:58,530 --> 00:08:59,580
Buttons!

175
00:09:02,170 --> 00:09:04,040
(gasps)
No!

176
00:09:05,670 --> 00:09:08,620
NO!

177
00:09:08,620 --> 00:09:11,340
No...!

178
00:09:16,270 --> 00:09:20,810
No, no!

179
00:09:23,860 --> 00:09:26,030
Well, tie me up
and brand me.

180
00:09:26,030 --> 00:09:27,280
Ya all's young again!

181
00:09:27,280 --> 00:09:29,650
And everybody's safe
and sound.

182
00:09:29,650 --> 00:09:30,790
What about Slugger?

183
00:09:30,780 --> 00:09:31,890
And Buttons?

184
00:09:31,900 --> 00:09:33,620
Don't worry.

185
00:09:33,620 --> 00:09:37,160
They're the safest
and soundest of any of us.

186
00:09:37,150 --> 00:09:40,650
(All giggle)

187
00:09:40,660 --> 00:09:44,880
Let's hard a port and
set sail for safe dry dock.

188
00:09:44,880 --> 00:09:48,640
I've got a better idea, Salty.
Let's go home instead?

